## 2026-04-03 - TokenTableView silently swallows invalid inline edit values with no user feedback
- Added `editError` state (boolean) to `TokenTableView`. When `commitEdit` detects `parseInlineValue` returns `null`, it sets `editError=true`, re-focuses the input, and returns without closing the cell — keeping the user in edit mode. The input border turns red (`border-red-500`) and a `title` tooltip says "Invalid value for this token type". Error clears automatically when the user modifies the input or cancels. `cancelEdit` also clears `editError`. `startEdit` resets it before opening.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/TokenTableView.tsx` ~L63, ~L137, ~L148, ~L161, ~L291
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

